# Mobile modal width

Never make dialog/modal forms full-width on mobile. Always leave horizontal inset so the overlay shows around the card.

## Required pattern

- Prefer the shared `DialogContent` default: `w-[calc(100%-2rem)]` (already in `src/components/ui/dialog.jsx`).
- When overriding `DialogContent` className, **keep** `w-[calc(100%-2rem)]` (or equivalent inset). Do not use bare `w-full` without side margin.
- Keep rounded corners on mobile (`rounded-2xl` / `rounded-xl`), not square edge-to-edge sheets unless explicitly requested.

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD
<DialogContent className="w-[calc(100%-2rem)] max-w-lg sm:max-w-2xl ...">

// ❌ BAD — edge-to-edge on small screens
<DialogContent className="w-full max-w-lg ...">
```
